summary: VEHICLE EXPERIENCED ACCELERATION SURGES.  *MR   THE SURGING OCCURRED AT RANDOM TIMES ABOVE 25 MPH.   THE ACCELERATION SURGE ALSO OCCURRED WITH THE CRUISE CONTROL ENGAGED.  ALSO THE MANUAL TRANSMISSION WOULD NOT SHIFT INTO FOURTH GEAR AT HIGHWAY SPEEDS.  IF A SHIFT WAS MISSED, THE TRANSMISSION WINDED UP BUT NO POWER WAS TRANSFERRED TO THE WHEELS.  WITH THE CLUTCH ENGAGED, THE TRANSMISSION COULD NOT BE PUT INTO GEAR UNTIL THE TRANSMISSION WINDED DOWN.     *TT    *JB
